# Safety and non-destructive behavior

**When this applies:** Any edit; special attention for env, auth, migrations, infra, or broad refactors.

**Do this:**
- Do not add secrets, API keys, or credentials to the repo. Do not assume production deployment permissions or force production automation.
- Do not run destructive shell commands (e.g. rm -rf on broad paths, force push to shared branches) without explicit user confirmation.
- Flag or call out edits to sensitive surfaces: env files, auth config, billing, migrations, infra configs. Prefer minimal, reversible changes there.
- Do not refactor business logic or product architecture solely for cleanliness; do not rename large parts of the codebase unless required.

**Full procedure:** AGENTS.md "Safety constraints" and "What requires approval before editing"; docs/Compliance-Boundaries.md.
